slidetranscripts.slidetranscript:
There are some fundamental changes coming with the new UCPath system in regards to funding and salary transfers.

We will outline them in this video.

If you wish to download a PDF with the content of this video, click the on-screen link.

Click to continue.

Among the changes taking place, here is what you should expect for UC Davis campus:

Funding Entry on New Positions will be handled by service channels.

Funding Updates to Existing positions will be handled by the Department fund and account administrators.

Salary Cost Transfers will also be handled by the department fund and account administrators.

Please note that Service Channels may also make funding updates when needed as per discussion with the department.

For UC Davis Health:

Medical Center employees (Chart H) will have all Funding Entry & Salary Cost Transfers done by Health Service Channel.


Schools of Health Funding Entry Updates and Salary Cost Transfers for Schools of Health will be distributed to the department administration. 

In other words, a School of Medicine department, such as Internal Medicine, will process their own Funding Entry updates and Salary Cost Transfers.

With new security roles, UC Davis departments and units will be required to identify who will be responsible for transactions in UCPath.

Finance users can have direct access to enter and approve funding entry and cost transfer transactions.

Please note that users with these roles do not have access to sensitive HR and payroll information.

Managers should consider who in their groups will be granted these roles.

Here are some key changes happening as we transition into UCPath.

Salary Cost Transfers, also known as SETs, will be processed in UCPath instead of in KFS.

KFS SET documents will continue to be available for a period after UCPath Go Live.

Funding Entry and Cost Transfer transactions have approval workflow.

Transactions require approval prior to being committed. Dept/Units need to identify who will be responsible for approvals for Funding Entry & Cost Transfers.

Funding Entry (used for funding distributions) does not determine if an employee is paid.

Employees will be paid as long as there is an active Job record even if the Funding Entry Page is blank or has expired funding.
And more changes

The Full Accounting Unit (FAU) will appear differently in UCPath.

A key change is that the Object Code will no longer be entered by the user, but rather derived by the system based on rules programmed by UCD.

It does not appear on screen, but will appear in reporting.

Also, differently from PPS, Org and Fund will be displayed, and a new FAU field is being introduced: the Budget Sub.

This field is used in the derivation of the Object Code and is selected by the user.

In addition, observe that at UCPath, the Sub- Account appears at the end of the string.

Composite Benefit Rate (CBR),

General, Automobile,and Employment Practices Liability (GAEL),

and Vacation Assessments will be assessed in UCPath.

Leaves, such as vacation, paid time off (PTO) and sick, will be paying earnings codes which will change the way they appear in the ledger.

Note that the financial assessment for vacation will continue even if the employee is over-the-max and is no longer accruing hours.

Departments need to closely monitor vacation accruals and encourage employees to take and report vacation.

Now take a look at how entries will appear in the ledger.

Observe that this is not a mock up of an actual report but rather an illustration of this new concept.

The display will look different from the current state due to Earnings Codes being paid.

For monthly employees, Regular (REG) pay will be decremented by the amount of leaves for example.

Because Monthly employees report in arrears, you will see these as separate entries.

For bi-weekly employees, the decrementing of REG occurs in the same row.

In UCPath, the pay line (or expense) for the leave, such as Vacation (VAC) occurs in Wages while the credit from the Liability Pool occurs in Benefits.

Click Next when you are ready to continue.

Now lets talk about Funding Entry in UCPath.

Payroll funding related data for a filled or unfilled position is entered via the Funding Entry Page, a standalone page in UCPath.
Funding Entry has a separate security role, thus allowing finance staff direct access in UCPath without granting access to HR information.
The Funding Entry Page is configured to accommodate the Location Full Accounting Unit (FAU), called Chartstring in UCPath.

Individual Chartstring values are validated upon entry into the page, and location defined Chartfield combinations are validated upon saving the page. The data cannot be saved if there is an invalid value.

The approval routing in UCPath follows HR Department, the new name for Home Department.
Each position has an HR Department.

This means that the approval workflow will only follow this path. If a Position has multiple departmental funding sources, it will only route to the HR Department approvers.

This will require coordination across departments for multiple funding

Take a look at this routing example.

Linda works at the Department of Internal Medicine, and she is funded by the College of Biological Sciences.

In order for Linda to get paid, a funding transaction is initiated in UCPath by Robert, the budget and finance analyst at the department of Internal Medicine.

Jane is the budget and finance manager in the Department of Internal Medicine. She approves the transaction in UCPath.

Ann is the fiscal officer at the College of Biological Sciences, she reviews Linda's payroll expense in financial reporting.

It is important to keep in mind that the HR department and the funding department must communicate before the entry takes place.

Alternatively, someone outside of the HR Department can also INITIATE the funding entry change. For example, Jackson from the College of Biological Sciences, could initiate the fund entry for Lindas position, however Jane, the approver in the department of Internal Medicine, where the position resides, will still be the approver of the transaction.

Notice that only users with row level security for the HR Department of the Position can initiate and/or approve transactions.

And remember, approval responsibility should comply with PPM Section 330-10. The link to the policy is available on this screen.

Click next to continue.

There are changes in the reports.

Report data from UCPath will be accessed through the Cognos System.

Here is a list of some of the reports that will be available in Cognos.

Click next to continue.

The KFS DS 340 Payroll Lien,Committed Salary Report will not be re-written.

The KFS DS 339 will be replaced by the Cognos Payroll Expense Distribution report.

Thank you for watching!

Visit the UC Davis UC Path website for more training resources and job aids.

If you have questions or suggestions, please drop us an email.

Click next to close this video.
